gw.api.web.aria

Class AriaInfoKey<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.web.aria.AriaInfoKey<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the value associated with the key

    public class AriaInfoKey<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A key for one of the values in an AriaInfo object. Keys are typed so the value associated with a particular key must always have the appropriate type. Keys also have a name, which is used as the name of a corresponding attribute on the client.

      • DROP_EFFECT

        public static final AriaInfoKey<AriaDropEffect> DROP_EFFECT
        Indicates what functions can be performed when the dragged object is released on the drop target. This allows assistive technologies to convey the possible drag options available to users, including whether a pop-up menu of choices is provided by the application. Typically, drop effect functions can only be provided once an object has been grabbed for a drag operation as the drop effect functions available are dependent on the object being dragged. Possibilities: copy move link execute popup Attribute: aria-dropeffect
